        AHEM_I_PRESUME                                                        = 11514,  -- <Ahem>! %, I presume.
        WELL_MET_GOOD_SIR_MADAM_MY_NAME_IS                                    = 11515,  -- Well met, good sir/madam]. My name is Alberic, and I have the pleasure of being Joachim's compatriot from Abyssea.
        AS_I_AM_PRESSED_FOR_TIME_YOU_MUST                                     = 11516,  -- As I am pressed for time, you must forgive me for forgoing pleasantries.
        THE_NORTHLANDS_OF_OUR_TWO_WORLDS_ARE_NOT                              = 11517,  -- The Northlands of our two worlds are not dissimilar: they both are shrouded in mystery and held in trepidation by folk.
        THAT_YOU_NOW_STAND_BEFORE_THIS_CAVERNOUS_MAW                          = 11518,  -- That you now stand before this cavernous maw, % in hand, is silent affirmation of your intent.
        FIRSTLY_YOU_WOULD_DO_WELL_TO_REMEMBER_THAT                            = 11519,  -- Firstly, you would do well to remember that the portal, despite its location in Xarcabard, leads in fact to the Uleguerand Range.
        REPORTS_SUGGEST_THAT_SUCH_MAWS_EXITING_INTO_ALTERNATE                 = 11520,  -- Reports suggest that such maws exiting into alternate locales are not altogether uncommon, although the scientific explanation for this phenomenon eludes our researchers still.
        FOR_OUR_INTENTS_AND_PURPOSES_HOWEVER_SUCH_MATTERS                     = 11521,  -- For our intents and purposes, however, such matters are of small import.
        THE_PROBLEMS_THAT_WANT_FOR_OUR_SOLVING_ARE                            = 11522,  -- The problems that want for our solving are far more urgent and dire in nature.
        THE_ULEGUERAND_RANGE_TWOULD_BE_NO_EXAGGERATION_TO                     = 11523,  -- The Uleguerand Range... 'Twould be no exaggeration to call that place a frozen hell on Abyssea. There, 'tis as if nature herself desires the eradication of mankind.
        THE_STRENGTH_YOUR_FOLK_POSSESS_IS_FABLED_AMONG                        = 11524,  -- The strength your folk possess is fabled among my people. Nevertheless, one can never be too prudent when one's life is at stake. I urge you to practice due caution as you traverse Uleguerand's white fields of death.
        IN_PARTICULAR_YOU_WOULD_DO_WELL_TO_STAY                               = 11525,  -- In particular, you would do well to stay on constant alert for a grotesquely overlarge diremite.
        OF_A_SIZE_TO_DWARF_ITS_COUSINS_THIS                                   = 11526,  -- Of a size to dwarf its cousins, this vermin has a spine-chilling relish for man-flesh. Needless to say, this predilection is proving to be highly unfortunate for folk who subsist in the range.
        ALL_EFFORTS_TO_SLAY_THE_SAVAGE_FIEND_HAVE                             = 11527,  -- All efforts to slay the savage fiend have thus far proven fruitless...and costly. To compound matters, the difficult terrain hinders our attempts to devise effective strategies. Be ever wary out there, %, lest you be caught unawares by this nightmare creature.
        HMM_TWOULD_APPEAR_MY_VISIT_IS_AT_AN                                   = 11528,  -- Hmm, 'twould appear my visit is at an end. I must needs return to Abyssea.
        I_PRAY_THAT_THE_HEAVENS_SHALL_GRANT_US                                = 11529,  -- I pray that the heavens shall grant us another meeting. Fare you well.
        AH_THE_HERO_OF_THE_HOUR_MAKES_HIS                                     = 11530,  -- Ah, the hero of the hour makes his/her] triumphant return!
        REPORTS_REACHED_ME_BUT_MOMENTS_AGO_OF_YOUR                            = 11531,  -- Reports reached me but moments ago of your epic victory over the menace of Uleguerand. Of your people's exceptional strength I was well aware, but you truly shine above the rest.
        NOW_THE_SOULS_OF_MY_COMRADES_WHO_FELL                                 = 11532,  -- Now the souls of my comrades who fell to the vile beast may rest in peace. My boundless gratitude is yours, %.
        I_SHOULD_BE_HONORED_IF_YOU_WOULD_ACCEPT                               = 11533,  -- I should be honored if you would accept this gift.
        CONSIDER_IT_A_SMALL_TOKEN_OF_MY_GRATITUDE                             = 11534,  -- Consider it a small token of my gratitude.
        TIS_CALLED                                                            = 11535,  -- %, 'tis called.
        AN_UNCOMMON_VARIETY_OF_THE_STONE_TIS_KNOWN                            = 11536,  -- An uncommon variety of the stone, 'tis known to unleash its full potential when wielded by a native of your world. It should serve you well in the battles to come.
        YOUR_VALOROUS_DEED_HAS_ALLOWED_HOPE_TO_TAKE                           = 11537,  -- Your valorous deed has allowed hope to take root again within the barren snowfields of Uleguerand. Yet our journey to salvation is far from over.
        THE_GREAT_CATACLYSM_TORE_ACROSS_THE_LAND_AS                           = 11538,  -- The great cataclysm tore across the land as steel rips through flesh, deeply scarring our world and the hearts of those who call it home.
        THE_WOUND_I_BEAR_WITHIN_BLEEDS_TO_THIS                                = 11539,  -- The wound I bear within bleeds to this day, yet I continue to fight in the hopes that the suffering can be ended.
        IN_THIS_AGE_OF_UNENDING_TORMENT_MANY_ARE                              = 11540,  -- In this age of unending torment, many are those who hurl curses at the heavens for what they regard as abandonment. I, for one, believe that man has always shaped his own destiny, and must continue to do so.
        THE_FATE_OF_MY_HOME_WORLD_SHALL_NOT                                   = 11541,  -- The fate of my home world shall not be one of destruction, this I solemnly vow. Even should my body turn to dust, I shall fight on.
        COUNTLESS_MYSTERIES_REMAIN_UNSOLVED_YET_ONE_THING_IS                  = 11542,  -- Countless mysteries remain unsolved, yet one thing is clear: the people of Abyssea cannot survive without the aid of you and yours. I beseech you, %. Stand with us in our darkest hour.
